<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="027" project="spaarke-daily-update-service-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add structured member_skipped warning logging for Contact-only members</title>
    <phase>3: W1 Producer — customData + stubs + membership (PR 3)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>1.5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>028</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, observability, refactoring</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies BFF observability surface in `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs` (or underlying `MembershipResolverService`). Load-bearing for AC-11 (Application Insights integration test). Touches BFF — CLAUDE.md §10 publish-size + CVE applies. ADR-028 + ADR-034 are binding (the Contact↔SystemUser mapping rationale lives in those).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>In `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs` (or the underlying `MembershipResolverService`), when a Contact-typed member is detected with `azureactivedirectoryobjectid` NULL (no SystemUser cross-ref), emit a structured `ILogger.LogWarning` with event name `member_skipped` and fields: `matterid`, `contactid`, `role`, `reason: "no_systemuser_mapping"`. Use ILogger structured-logging template syntax so Application Insights captures the fields as columns, not just the message string.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. BFF observability specialist with knowledge of ILogger structured-logging templates + Application Insights field extraction.</role>

  <goal>The membership resolution code path emits a structured `member_skipped` warning event with the 4 required fields whenever an unmappable Contact member is encountered. The event is captured by Application Insights as searchable columns (not just a plain message). Build + tests pass. Publish-size delta documented.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-11 (line 154) requires structured logging when the membership service detects a Contact member with NULL azureactivedirectoryobjectid. Such members cannot be resolved to a SystemUser (per ADR-028 canonical mapping), so they are silently skipped today — which is acceptable behavior but lacks visibility. The structured warning provides ops visibility + lets task 028 assert AC-11 via Application Insights integration test (or a mock-ILogger unit test). MUST use template syntax `LogWarning("member_skipped matter {MatterId} contact {ContactId} role {Role} reason {Reason}", matterId, contactId, role, reason)` so field-extraction works.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/shared/Spaarke.Core/Services/MembershipResolverService.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutorTests.cs</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Contact ↔ SystemUser cross-ref via azureactivedirectoryobjectid is the canonical mapping. Logging this gap MUST NOT change the mapping policy — just adds visibility.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-034">Membership resolution stays inside LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor / MembershipResolverService. Do NOT add a new logger service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — publish-size + CVE per task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene — publish-size + CVE per task. Placement decision: logging lives at the resolution site (membership executor or resolver service); use existing ILogger injection — no new types.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST use ILogger structured-logging template syntax (not string interpolation). Event name MUST be `member_skipped` (snake_case). Field names: `matterid`, `contactid`, `role`, `reason: "no_systemuser_mapping"`. MUST NOT silently drop the member without logging.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-034-user-record-membership-resolution.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/node-executor-authoring.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge files. Read FR-11 + AC-11.</step>
    <step order="2">Locate the Contact-resolution code path: read `LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs` + `MembershipResolverService.cs` to find where Contact members are filtered to SystemUsers via azureactivedirectoryobjectid.</step>
    <step order="3">Identify the precise point where a Contact-with-NULL-azureactivedirectoryobjectid is currently dropped (filter/where/skip path). This is the logging site.</step>
    <step order="4">Confirm ILogger is already injected at that site. If not, add it via constructor injection (existing DI pattern in the file).</step>
    <step order="5">Add `_logger.LogWarning("member_skipped matter {MatterId} contact {ContactId} role {Role} reason {Reason}", matterId, contactId, role, "no_systemuser_mapping")` at the drop site. Use template syntax — NOT string interpolation.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — fix compile errors.</step>
    <step order="7">Run existing tests `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter FullyQualifiedName~LookupUserMembership` to confirm no regression.</step>
    <step order="8">Run publish-size check + CVE check per CLAUDE.md §10.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 027 status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="10">Document the logging-site decision (executor vs resolver) + publish-size delta in `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build/test/publish .NET</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor.cs (or src/server/shared/Spaarke.Core/Services/MembershipResolverService.cs)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Code path that drops Contact-with-NULL-azureactivedirectoryobjectid emits ILogger.LogWarning with event name member_skipped.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Warning uses structured template syntax (not string interpolation) — {MatterId}, {ContactId}, {Role}, {Reason} placeholders.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Reason field value is literal string "no_systemuser_mapping".</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Member is still skipped (behavior unchanged) — logging adds visibility only.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build + existing tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta + CVE check recorded.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>Spec FR-11 line 154; AC-11 line 155. Hint: the logging site may live in `MembershipResolverService` (shared Spaarke.Core) rather than the executor — read both files first. If in Spaarke.Core, the publish-size impact on BFF should be near-zero (just an extra log statement). Hint: task 028 will add the xUnit fixture mocking ILogger to assert this event fires — that's where AC-11 gets test coverage; this task just lands the log call.</notes>

